				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${R}_{\mathrm{MMC}}= \prod_{i=1}^{N}{R}_{\mathrm{IGBT}}.$$\end{document}

However, it is worth noting that in this research, the SMTR loop has been incorporated into the individual DC capacitor balancing with the aim of equalizing the thermal stress among all the SMs. This is assumed to translate into equal reliability and lifetime expectancy of the SMs. Based on the foregoing, (14) can be rewritten as:15RMMC=RIGBTN.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${R}_{\mathrm{MMC}}= {R}_{\mathrm{IGBT}}^{N}.$$\end{document}

According to [39], the reliability of an MMC can be equated to the reliability of one arm due to symmetry. As such, the parameter N\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$N$$\end{document} in (15) is the number of SMs in one arm of the converter.

The failure rate of the MMC system can be calculated as:16λMMC=-logRMMC.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\lambda }_{\mathrm{MMC}}= -\mathrm{log}\left({R}_{\mathrm{MMC}}\right).$$\end{document}

The MTTF of the MMC MTTFMMC\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{MTTF}}_{\mathrm{MMC}}$$\end{document} can be obtained as:17MTTFMMC=1λMMC.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
